<h2 id="why-waterfall-fails">Why Waterfall fails</h2>

<p>‚Ä¢Waterfall projects have 3x the failure rate (29% vs. 9%) and 1/3 the success rate (14% vs. 42%) of Agile projects (Standish Group, CHAOS Report 2012)</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Inventor of Waterfall <a href="http://pascal.gugenberger.net/thoughts/waterfall-accident.html">Winston W. Royce</a> described in his academic paper written in 1970 that it was ‚Äúrisky and invites failure‚Äù and went on to describe Incremental development.</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Recent failed waterfall projects that scrapped</p>

<p>‚Ä¢UK Govt. <a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2040259/NHS-IT-project-failure-Labours-12bn-scheme-scrapped.html">¬£12 Billion</a> for national program for NHS IT</p>

<p>‚Ä¢US Air Force - 6 year project with cost of <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/09/technology/air-force-stumbles-over-software-modernization-project.html?_r=0">$1.3 Billion</a></p>

<p>‚Ä¢QLD Health <a href="http://www.cio.com.au/article/426920/qld_health_payroll_it_train_wrecks_preventable/">$1.2 Billion</a></p>

<h2 id="agile-vs-waterfall">Agile vs. Waterfall</h2>

<p>Agile techniques deliver business-critical solutions at 40% lower cost, 50% faster and with significantly greater fit and quality.</p>

<p><a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chrismckelt/chrismckelt.github.io/master/_posts/posts/images//2018/08/image-5.png"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chrismckelt/chrismckelt.github.io/master/_posts/posts/images//image_thumb-5.png" alt="image" title="image" /></a></p>

<p>Source - ¬© Standish Group CHAOS report 1994 ‚Äì 2010. Sample size over 40,000 completed IT Projects.</p>

<h3 id="why-change">Why Change?</h3>

<p>History has proven that those businesses that do adapt die.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/chunkamui/2012/01/18/how-kodak-failed/">Kodak</a> failed to embrace digital cameras</p>

<h2 id="how-will-agile-help-us">How will Agile help us?</h2>

<p>‚Ä¢Reduce time to market</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Reduce risk by finding errors earlier in the process</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Early access to the software during the life cycle</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Greater flexibility to change</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Early cancellation(or failure) hurts less</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Reduced defect count</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Maintain compliance levels and auditory requirements</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Improved ROI</p>

<p>‚Ä¢Improved transparency for stake holders/management</p>
